Is that true? The current <a href="http://dev.w3.org/html5/markup/base.html" class="postlink">editor's draft</a> says:<br /><blockquote class="uncited"><div><br />href = URI<br />The base URL for the document.<br /></div></blockquote><br />And from what I understand (I'm never quite sure about this part), what they describe there is necessarily absolute (as in <span style="font-style: italic">scheme://stuff</span>).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=989">zneak</a> — Mon May 10, 2010 10:15 pm</p><hr />
