<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4294&amp;p=5856#p5856"><![CDATA[
Hello everyone,<br /><br />I was using the &lt;base&gt; tag on a project of mine for rather complex purposes, and I found out my code didn't work with Firefox. After a lot of testing, I found out that Firefox cannot handle relative paths in the href attribute of &lt;base&gt;, because the standard says so.<br /><br />What's the rationale behind this? To me, it's downright idiotic.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=989">zneak</a> — Mon May 10, 2010 2:44 am</p><hr />
